article.description: — Cameron Brown had 20 points and Saint Joseph's (Pa.) beat La Salle 71-59 on Monday.
article.headline: Brown's 20 lead Saint Joseph's (Pa.) over La Salle 71-59
article.linkText: Brown's 20 lead Saint Joseph's (Pa.) over La Salle 71-59
article.story:
PHILADELPHIA -- — Cameron Brown had 20 points and Saint Joseph's (Pa.) beat La Salle 71-59 on Monday.

Brown was 6 of 12 shooting, including 4 for 7 from distance, and went 4 for 4 from the line for the Hawks (8-10, 2-4 Atlantic 10 Conference). Erik Reynolds II scored 19 points and added five rebounds. Lynn Greer III was 5 of 9 shooting and 1 of 3 from the free throw line to finish with 12 points.

The Explorers (8-10, 2-3) were led in scoring by Fousseyni Drame, who finished with 24 points, 13 rebounds and four steals. Khalil Brantley added seven points, five assists and five steals for La Salle. Jhamir Brickus also put up six points.

------
